    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-03-05</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-04-15T14:12:03Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Puppies Assisting Wounded Servicemembers for Veterans Therapy Act or the PAWS for Veterans Therapy Act</b></p> <p>This bill implements a program and a policy related to service dog therapy for veterans. Specifically, the bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to implement a five-year pilot program to assess the effectiveness of addressing post-deployment mental health and post-traumatic stress disorder through a method where veterans train service dogs for veterans with disabilities.</p> <p>The bill also authorizes the VA to provide service dogs to veterans with mental illnesses, regardless of whether they have a mobility impairment.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
